"v.制止(血液)，止住 【英】 v.制止(血液)，止住( to check or stop the flowing) 【考】 damp : vibration / stanch : flow(制止振动/制止流动) 【记】 stan(站)＋ch→让(血 液)站住→止住 【例】 stanch a leak in a ship(堵住船上的漏洞 ) v. 止住血液 【记】stan站, ch－让血液站住－止住 【类】damp: vibration = stanch: flow制止振动 = 制止流动 【记】源自stand； stand 停止 + check 阻止；stitch 缝合→缝合伤口→止血 【相关】standing 停滞的， standing water 死水, staunch 坚定的，starch 上浆使坚硬 stanch (v.)  ""to stop the flow of"" (especially of blood), early 14c., from Old French estanchier ""cause to cease flowing (of blood), stop, hinder; extinguish (of fire); tire, exhaust, drain"" (Modern French étancher), from Vulgar Latin *stancare, perhaps contracted from *stagnicare, from Latin stagnum ""pond, pool"" (see stagnate). But Barnhart says it probably is from Latin stantio, present participle of stare ""to stand."""
